The biggest draw this site has, and the main thing that sets us apart from simple creepypasta and fanfic, is that the SCP articles and related materials set a believable and realistic tone.

An SCP article is intended to read as a summary of containment procedures and the potential risks of failing to contain an SCP object written by a professional, clinical individual who knows what he's doing.

Lines like "we must have constant vigilance to be sure that the containment center does not become an icy waste." read like fanfic written by a high school student, not like a professional brief written by a serious scientist. They seriously breach character, and strongly damage suspention of disbelief. Frankly, it's a shitty thing to do to your article.

The entire final addendum adds precisely nothing to this article, and takes away quite a bit. You would be better off removing it.

"But someone else fucked up too!" is never a valid excuse.







