I enjoyed the concept, besides two little bits which bug me.

First, -37 degree vapor getting spit into a room is never going to actually reduce its temperature to -37 degrees. 1,000,000 parts of -37 degree air combined with one part of 10 degree air will average out to something a bit over the minimum threshold to set this thing off, as it's written.

Second, is this thing actually spitting out air or just converting the current air to a different temperature/humidity? The two imply very different effects. If it's actually spitting gas out, it'd be interesting to see what happens if you try to cover that up with something like a weather balloon.

Besides those, interesting SPC.





